title: The Essential Irish Ballads Collection
description:
We bought this CD in Killarney a few weeks ago and listened to it while traveling the country.  I hope you enjoy it as much as we have.  Ripped in 320kbps.

30-track double CD featuring definitive versions of classic Irish ballads. The inspirational "The Fields Of Athenry" (Paddy Reilly) and "The Rare Old Times" (Dublin City Ramblers) sit comfortably alongside superb interpretations of 'adopted' songs such as "The Green Fields Of France" (The Furey Brothers and Davy Arthur). Other tracks include "Muirsheen Durkin" (Johnny McEvoy), "Grace" (Barleycorn), "The Leaving Of Liverpool" (Patsy Watchorn), "Lannigan's Ball" (The Jolly Beggarmen) and "The Humour Is On Me Now" (Ronnie Drew).

Click "Files" above to see the list of all the songs.
